<br>
I've regularly cast it on pulls, and never disrupted a pull doing it yet.<br>
<br>
Malo is also unresistable debuff, so you might as well get it in plenty early so everyone else has plenty of time to cast their debuffs.<br>
<br>
MaloSINI can be stacked on top of it, and depending on mobs can be resisted anywhere from never to every time.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes you need all of that PLUS occlusion of sound from bards to get a slow to land, depending on what zone/mobs you're fighting.  But that's all further down the line -- casting the malo part is easy and you should just get it out of the way.  I don't know how many (thousands of?) times I've cast it, but I've never gained aggro or been summoned or hit for it yet.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uluucasmaximus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luucas Maximus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/30/02 12:56:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11127.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Monk CT camp?</span><hr size=1> I am not overly familiar with the mudbowl camp, but we saw bloodclaw up on the way to fear and decided to pop him since the MT sorta needed some nice legs. Anyways, from what i saw there were 3 static spawns in that room (raptors) and he was a pat who seemed to move between the 3 of them. Hope that helps. <p><B><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97338>Luuc Up</A></B><BR>
